# AI Observability Stack

# Introduction

AI Observability is the process of monitoring, tracing, evaluating, debugging, and analyzing AI systems in production environments.

Modern LLM applications require observability because AI systems are:
- Non-deterministic
- Distributed
- Expensive
- Context-driven
- Tool-integrated

AI observability helps teams monitor:
- Prompt behavior
- Hallucinations
- Token usage
- Latency
- Cost
- RAG quality
- Multi-agent workflows
- Infrastructure performance

---

# Why AI Observability Matters

Without observability:
- Hallucinations go unnoticed
- Costs explode
- Latency increases
- AI failures become difficult to debug
- RAG systems silently degrade

---

# Goals of AI Observability

| Goal | Description |
|---|---|
| Reliability | Stable AI behavior |
| Visibility | End-to-end tracing |
| Debugging | Faster root-cause analysis |
| Optimization | Cost & performance tuning |
| Evaluation | AI quality monitoring |
| Governance | Auditing & compliance |

